In Rugby Union, the 'try' score is awarded to either team when they successfully convert their first-half penalty kick or drop goal attempt into an unconverted try (i.e., scored after two minutes). The number of points that can be earned from this type of conversion varies depending on the rules set by each league/tournament:

1) In Premiership Rugby, tries count as three points for both teams;
2) In Pro14, tries count as four points for both teams;
3) In Super Rugby Aotearoa, tries count as five points for both teams;

Sadie King is not an actual character on the British soap opera "Emmerdale." The name refers to one of several fictional characters who have appeared as guests or recurring cast members over its many seasons, including:
- Sadie King (played by Sarah Parish) from season two through sixteen;
- Sadie King (played by Lydia Rose Warren) from seventeen until present day.

